headline: Phillips 66 Urges Shareholders to Vote Against Elliott at Annual Meeting
summary: Phillips 66’s board of directors is again pushing against one of its largest investors—Elliott Investment Management—with a letter to shareholders detailing how to vote against the investment company at its upcoming annual meeting.

headline: Elliott Launches "Streamline 66" Podcast Featuring 1:1 Conversations with Its Best-in-Class Director Nominees
summary: Elliott Investment Management L.P. ("Elliott"), which manages funds that together make it a top five shareholder in Phillips 66 (NYSE: PSX) (the "Company" or "Phillips"), today announced the launch of the Streamline 66 Podcast, a new series that will feature 1:1 conversations with Elliott's highly qualified director nominees ("Nominees" or "Nominee"), as well as industry experts. Episodes can be accessed on Streamline66.com, and are available on Apple, Spotify and everywhere podcasts are heard.

headline: Phillips 66 Files Definitive Proxy Statement and Issues Letter to Shareholders
summary: HOUSTON, April 08, 2025--Phillips 66 announced that it has filed its definitive proxy materials with the U.S. SEC in connection with its Annual Meeting of Shareholders.
